Chevron May Be Expelled From Brazil After Oil Spill, EFE Says

-- B y   F r a n c i s c o   M a r c e l i n o
-- 
2011-12-03T20:31:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-03/chevron-may-be-expelled-from-brazil-after-oil-spill-efe-says.html
Chevron Corp. (CVX)  may be expelled from
 Brazil  if it doesn’t fulfill its agreement with the government
to repair the damage caused by an  oil spill  off the country’s
coastline, EFE reported, citing Energy Minister Edison Lobao.  Lobao said Chevron must pay a 50 million real fine
($27.9 million) and also take the responsibility for the
environmental damages, according to the news service.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Francisco Marcelino in  Sao Paulo  at 
 mdeoliveira@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier in New York at 
 swier@bloomberg.net  